Description: Fragment of oval handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora from neck join to sharpish turn. Clay near fine pink-buff; cream slip. Rectangular stamp with caduceus symbol.
Curator's comments: Name Dion. Trimmed. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0344.07
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0825)
